<TITLE> JP to sit with advisers: party leader </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 9 (bdnews24.com)  The government will sit with Jatiya Party leaders in an informal meeting Wednesday evening, a JP leader said. Acting JP chairman Anisul Islam Mahmud told bdnews24.com that an adviser had invited them for informal talks. "Those advisers who had a meeting with Awami League leaders want to sit with us too," he said. Anisul did not disclose the venue for the meeting. Law adviser Hassan Ariff, communications adviser Ghulam Quader, local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal, education and commerce adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman and foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury held a meeting with AL leaders on Monday. The government approached both factions of the BNP on Tuesday for similar informal talks leading up to the proposed formal dialogues between the government and political parties. bdnew
